 did. London is a wonderful city it's just so expensive.One of the best things about it doesn't cost any money. My favorite thing is just walking around and admiring the buildings and the history of the city. Walking in Harrods and having a dessert at the Food court area. It was totally packed! A one day metro pass is about u$s 10 with the conversion and is the cheapest way of getting around. (Although this weekend the Circle and District lines (green and yellow) have been closed down for maintenance. Also, it's been sprinkling rain all weekend which is a bit of a bummer but there have been glimpses of some sun. I recommend this hotel if you aren't on any kind of budget. Great service, staff and location!	
